You are here: Salesforce Help | Docs | Analytics | What’s the Difference Between Analytics Tab and Analytics Studio?

The business user path leads to ready-to-explore dashboards and lenses in curated apps. For this path, work in the CRM Analytics tab to run apps and collaborate with coworkers over dashboards.

The builder path leads to ready-to-explore datasets and ready-to-edit apps, dashboards, and lenses. For this path, work in the Analytics Studio to browse your assets and build new ones.

This table summarizes the differences between the Analytics tab and the Analytics Studio.

ACTION ANALYTICS TAB ANALYTICS STUDIO
Create Annotate Set Notification Watchlist Collections Favorite Edit Full Screen Clip to Designer Clone in New Tab Save Share Delete
